{
  "message": "Mission received. Building engineered hiring pipeline.",
  "workflow": {
    "nodes": [
      {
        "label": "Hiring Demand Triggered",
        "category": "trigger",
        "description": "Business need initiates hiring for 5 engineers within 2 months",
        "content": "Trigger event: Formal hiring request submitted via HRIS (e.g., Workday, BambooHR) by department head with executive approval. Payload includes role titles (e.g., Senior Backend Engineer), budget allocation, timeline constraints (start date within 60 days), and headcount justification. Configuration: Set up automated webhook to capture request ID, requester email, and attached documents (business case, org chart). Steps: 1) Verify request against quarterly planning in Notion or Jira; 2) Log trigger in ATS (Greenhouse or Lever) with priority flag; 3) Notify recruiting lead via Slack/Email with SLA of 24-hour response. Tools: Integrate Zapier or custom API to sync with calendar for milestone tracking. Ensure data includes compliance checks (EEO, budget codes) and kick off workflow only after all signatures are digitally captured in DocuSign."
      },
      {
        "label": "Define Job Requirements and Strategy",
        "category": "action",
        "description": "Create detailed job descriptions and hiring plan aligned with goals",
        "content": "Action steps: 1) Schedule kickoff meeting with hiring manager and team leads within 48 hours using Calendly; 2) Draft job descriptions using templates in Google Docs, including must-have skills (e.g., Python, AWS), nice-to-haves, and cultural fit criteria; 3) Define KPIs: target response rate (≥50 applications per role), diversity goals (e.g., 30% underrepresented groups), and sourcing channels mix (40% referrals, 30% LinkedIn, 20% niche boards, 10% agencies). Tools: Use ATS integrations to auto-populate fields; benchmark salaries with Levels.fyi or Compaas. Output: Approved JD stored in shared drive with version control; create project plan in Asana with milestones (sourcing complete by day 15, first interviews by day 20). Assign owner: Recruiting Coordinator; include checklist for legal review and budget alignment."
      },
      {
        "label": "Execute Multi-Channel Sourcing",
        "category": "action",
        "description": "Proactively source candidates beyond LinkedIn using targeted outreach",
        "content": "Numbered steps: 1) Activate LinkedIn Recruiter seats with Boolean searches (e.g., 'site:github.com Java AND spring boot') and InMail campaigns (template: personalized value prop); 2) Launch referral program via Teamable or Gr8People with bonuses ($3k per hire); 3) Post on niche boards (Stack Overflow, AngelList) and attend virtual events (Meetup, conferences); 4) Run targeted ads on Google/Facebook with tracking UTM codes. Tools: Use HireEZ or SeekOut for diversity sourcing; set up drip campaigns in Outreach.io for passive candidates. Error handling: Monitor response rates daily; if <20% InMail acceptance, A/B test subject lines. Owner: Sourcer; weekly report on pipeline health (candidates per role ≥10). Include criteria: prioritize candidates with active GitHub projects or published tech talks."
      },
      {
        "label": "Screen Resumes and Initial Contact",
        "category": "action",
        "description": "Filter applications and conduct phone screens to qualify candidates",
        "content": "Steps: 1) Use ATS (Greenhouse) to parse resumes with keyword scoring (weights for skills, experience); 2) Recruiter performs 15-minute phone screens using structured script (questions on motivation, relocation); 3) Score candidates on rubric (1-5 scale for technical fit, communication); 4) Schedule Calendly links for next step if score ≥4. Tools: Integrate with CodeSignal for quick tech assessments; log notes in ATS with tags. Error handling: If pass-through rate <30%, refine rubric or retrain recruiters. Owner: Recruiter; SLA of 72 hours from application to contact. Include checklist: verify work authorization, salary expectations, and availability. Output: Qualified candidate list with summaries for interview panel; if insufficient volume (<5 per role), trigger feedback loop to adjust sourcing."
      },
      {
        "label": "Schedule and Coordinate Interviews",
        "category": "review",
        "description": "Human approval on interview plan and panel assignments",
        "content": "Approval criteria: 1) Interview panel must include hiring manager, tech lead, and culture add representative; 2) Schedule within 5 business days of screening, using tools like GoodTime or Calendly to avoid conflicts; 3) Set interview duration (45 min tech, 30 min behavioral) and format (virtual via Zoom with recorded consent). Who reviews: Recruiting manager approves panel composition and timeline; escalate to VP if delays >2 days. SLA: 24-hour turnaround for scheduling. Steps: Send calendar invites with prep materials (JD, scoring guide); confirm room/tech setup. Escalation path: If panelists unavailable, use backup list or adjust dates. Include policy: No interviews without pre-briefing on bias training. Output: Calendarized interview slots with candidate confirmations."
      },
      {
        "label": "Conduct Structured Interviews",
        "category": "action",
        "description": "Execute technical and behavioral interviews with consistent evaluation",
        "content": "Numbered steps: 1) Panelists use standardized question bank (e.g., from Karat for coding, STAR for behavioral) in centralized doc; 2) Technical round: Live coding on CoderPad or HackerRank, assessing problem-solving (30 min); 3) Cultural fit round: Values alignment using scorecard (e.g., 'Ownership', 'Curiosity'); 4) Collect feedback immediately via ATS form (scale 1-10 with comments). Tools: Record sessions (with permission) for calibration; use BrightHire for note-taking. Error handling: If inter-rater reliability <80%, hold calibration meeting. Owner: Interview panel; debrief within 24 hours. Include criteria: Pass requires average score ≥7 and no red flags (e.g., poor collaboration). Output: Compiled feedback report for decision node; if inconsistencies, loop back for re-interview."
      },
      {
        "label": "Final Candidate Selection and Approval",
        "category": "review",
        "description": "Hiring committee reviews feedback and approves offers",
        "content": "Approval criteria: 1) Consensus from panel (≥80% agreement); 2) Reference checks via Checkster or manual calls (3 references min); 3) Budget alignment with compensation band (data from Radford). Who reviews: Hiring committee (manager, director, HRBP); escalate to CFO for offers above band. SLA: Decision within 48 hours post-interviews. Steps: Compile scorecards in ATS; hold roundtable to debate ties; use rubric: technical (40%), cultural (30%), experience (30%). Escalation: If no candidate meets bar, pause and refine requirements. Include policy: No offer without background check initiation. Output: Approved candidate list with offer details; if rejections, document reasons to refine screening process. Tools: Lever analytics for decision tracking."
      },
      {
        "label": "Extend Offer and Initiate Onboarding",
        "category": "output",
        "description": "Deliver offers and kick off pre-boarding for new hires",
        "content": "Deliverable format: Formal offer letter via Docusign with components: salary, equity, benefits, start date. Distribution: Sent by recruiting lead with follow-up call within 24 hours. Success metrics: Target acceptance rate ≥85%, time-to-offer ≤5 days from approval. Steps: 1) Negotiate using scripted ranges (10% flexibility); 2) Upon acceptance, trigger onboarding in BambooHR: IT setup (laptop request via ServiceNow), access grants (Slack, GitHub), and orientation schedule; 3) Send welcome package and assign buddy. Tools: Integrate with ADP for payroll; use Trello for pre-boarding checklist. Monitor: Track decline reasons (e.g., counteroffer) to adjust future offers. Output: Signed offers stored digitally; onboarding timeline shared with manager; report hiring completion to stakeholders with KPIs (e.g., diversity met, cost-per-hire)."
      }
    ],
